Reasoning: The paper discusses consistency models for replicated data stores, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific consistency model discussed is causal consistency, which is commonly used in distributed databases (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance implications of different implementations of read-only transactions, which could fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
